additional_info:
For my browser I use the Noia 4 theme to get the grey gradient style however using the Default or Light theme works just as well.

userChrome.css should be updated with the following css to improve the overall effect:
<code>/* Hide main tabs toolbar */
#TabsToolbar {
	visibility: collapse;
}

/* Hide (i) in URL bar next to SSL padlock */
#identity-icon {
	width: 0 !important;
}

/* Adjust lock icon to be closer to edge */
#identity-box {
	padding-inline-start: 2px !important;
}

/* Hide sidebar header, when using Tree Style Tab. */
#sidebar-box[sidebarcommand="treestyletab_piro_sakura_ne_jp-sidebar-action"] #sidebar-header {
	visibility: collapse;
}</code>

The CSS for the style code is to be added into the "Extra style rules for sidebar contents" box under the Advanced settings for the Tree Style Tabs extension.
<strong>Make sure you remove the first line of the code!</strong>
This style is best used with the Plain or Mixed theme selected in Tree Stle Tabs.
If there is a problem with the tabs overlapping when applying the CSS code, switch the TST theme to reset the spacing.

css:
/* DELETE THE BELOW LINE! - THIS IS JUST ADDED TO ALLOW SCRIPT TO UPLOAD TO STYLISH */
@namespace url(http://www.mozilla.org/keymaster/gatekeeper/there.is.only.xul);
/* This CSS is to be added to the "Extra style rules for sidebar contents" box under the Advanced settings for the Tree Style Tabs extension */

/* Hide close buttons on tabs. */
.tab .closebox {
	visibility: collapse;
}

/* Hide sound playing/muted button. */
/*.sound-button {
	display: none !important;
}*/

/* Hide 'new tab' button. */
/*.newtab-button {
	display: none;
}*/


/* ##### THEME ############################################ */
#tabbar {
	border-right: 1px solid #1d1d1d;
	box-shadow: none !important;
	background-color: #aaaaaa;
}

.tab {
	background-color: #eeeeee;
	border-color: #999999;
	box-shadow: none !important;
	height: 25px !important;
}
.tab .label {
	color: rgba(0,0,0,0.75) !important;
}
.tab:hover {
	background-color: #ddeeff !important;
}
.tab:hover .label {
	color: rgba(0,0,0,1) !important;
}

.tab.discarded {
	background-color: #eeeeee;
}
.tab.discarded .label {
	color: rgba(0,0,0,0.35) !important;
	font-style: italic;
}

.tab.active {
	background-color: #bbccee;
}
.tab.active .label {
	font-weight: bold;
	color: rgba(0,0,0,1) !important;
}
.tab.active:hover {
	background-color: #ccddff!important;
}

.tab.unread .label {
	color: rgba(200,0,0,1) !important;
}
.tab.discarded.unread .label {
	color: rgba(200,0,0,0.5) !important;
}

/* Add drop shadow to bottom of tabs*/
div {
	box-shadow: 5px 5px 5px #888888;
}

/* Adjust style for tab that is muted. */
.tab.muted {
	opacity: 0.5;
}

/* Adjust style for tab that has sound playing. */
.tab.sound-playing .favicon::after {
	content: '';
	position: absolute;
	top: 50%;
	left: 50%;
	border-radius: 50%;
	background: #ee9999;
	animation: pulse 2s ease-out 0s infinite;
	z-index: -1;
	opacity: 0;
}

/* pulse animation for sound playing tab */
@keyframes pulse {
	0% {
		width: 0px;
		height: 0px;
		opacity: 1;
	}
	100% {
		width: 350px;
		height: 350px;
		opacity: 0;
		top: calc(50% - 175px);
		left: calc(50% - 175px);
	}
}
